Evans also found that the sensitivity level of the low-energy sensor is a factor in determining the reflectivity received at the sensor [9]. The sensitivity level represents a threshold below which the reflected return is indistinguishable from sensor noise. A sensitivity factor, %, is incorporated in the simulation to define the appropriate sensitivity level required to detect a hardbody's return as well as represent the physical limitations of the sensor.

